# Stack Constraints

## NEVER replace these technologies
- Frontend: Next.js (App Router), shadcn/ui, Tailwind CSS, TanStack Query, React Hook Form
- Backend: NestJS
- Database: PostgreSQL + Prisma ORM
- Observability: Prometheus, Grafana, Loki, Sentry
- Infrastructure: Docker Compose

## Frontend rules
- ALWAYS use shadcn/ui components — never raw `<input>`, `<button>`, `<select>` HTML elements
- ALWAYS use TanStack Query (`useQuery`, `useMutation`) for server state — never `useEffect` + `fetch`
- ALWAYS use React Hook Form + Zod for forms — never uncontrolled inputs or manual state
- ALWAYS use App Router patterns — never Pages Router (`pages/` directory)
- Server Components by default; add `'use client'` only when interactivity requires it

## Backend rules
- ALWAYS use NestJS decorators and DI — never plain Express handlers
- ALWAYS validate request bodies with class-validator DTOs
- ALWAYS use Prisma for database access — never raw SQL or other ORMs

## Observability rules
- NEVER remove Prometheus metric registration
- NEVER remove Loki log calls from scenario handlers
- NEVER remove Sentry.captureException from system_error scenario

## Enforcement
Violations of these rules require explicit justification in a PR description.
